WEBVTT

00:01.209 --> 00:03.253
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:03.336 --> 00:05.964
I don't see her making it
through the night.

00:06.047 --> 00:07.507
RANDALL:
We're good now.

00:07.590 --> 00:10.051
You made us good.

00:10.135 --> 00:12.345
You tell him hey.

00:15.724 --> 00:16.933
Hey.

00:17.976 --> 00:19.019
Hey.

00:19.102 --> 00:20.937
I'm pregnant.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.647
You're gonna be a grandfather.

00:22.731 --> 00:26.151
I'm not worried about
forgetting about the big stuff.

00:26.234 --> 00:28.653
It's the regular...

00:28.737 --> 00:30.780
Saturday
when the kids were little,

00:30.864 --> 00:33.366
a day when nothing big
really happened.

00:33.450 --> 00:35.118
We were just laughing

00:35.201 --> 00:37.412
and playing
pin the tail on the donkey.

00:37.495 --> 00:40.040
That's the stuff
I'm not ready to let go of yet.

00:41.291 --> 00:43.585
(birds chirping)

00:56.890 --> 00:59.642
-Mm. Hey.
-Hey.

01:00.977 --> 01:02.395
Mm.

01:03.521 --> 01:05.523
(takes deep breath)

01:07.067 --> 01:10.820
Did you know you have
a tiny little scar

01:10.904 --> 01:13.406
-underneath your eyebrow?
-Mm-hmm. Yeah.

01:14.449 --> 01:16.368
Yeah.

01:16.451 --> 01:19.329
I never noticed it before.

01:19.412 --> 01:21.122
Yeah. (inhales deeply)

01:21.206 --> 01:24.417
It comes out
when I'm in the sun,

01:24.501 --> 01:26.461
and I got a little sun
the other day.

01:26.544 --> 01:29.964
I can't believe
I never noticed it.

01:32.384 --> 01:35.011
(clears throat) So...

01:35.095 --> 01:37.013
-when I was a little girl...
-Mm-hmm.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.973
...there was this little
playground right by my house

01:39.057 --> 01:41.685
that my dad would take me to
sometimes,

01:41.768 --> 01:45.480
and it had one of
those really lame slides

01:45.563 --> 01:48.358
<i>-that would give you burn marks</i>
<i>on your butt. Mm-hmm.</i>
<i>-Oh, yeah. Yeah.</i>

01:48.441 --> 01:50.360
And, um, you know,

01:50.443 --> 01:52.529
one of those weird
old rocking horse things

01:52.612 --> 01:54.030
that only had one eye.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.949
<i>The springy ones.</i>

01:56.032 --> 01:57.909
-Yeah, yeah.
-Totally creeped me out.

01:57.992 --> 02:02.622
But then
there was this one swing.

02:02.706 --> 02:04.499
God, I loved that swing.

02:06.251 --> 02:09.004
And he would push me on it.

02:09.087 --> 02:12.424
And one time,
I remember I turned around

02:12.507 --> 02:15.552
on the way back down, and
my dad wasn't paying attention,

02:15.635 --> 02:19.305
and his watch clocked me
right above the eye.

02:19.389 --> 02:20.807
Hmm.

02:20.890 --> 02:22.934
He felt so bad,

02:23.018 --> 02:26.521
but I didn't care because
him pushing me in that swing

02:26.604 --> 02:28.106
was just my favorite thing

02:28.189 --> 02:29.441
<i>in the entire world, you know?</i>

02:29.524 --> 02:32.652
DAVE:
And we swing.

02:32.736 --> 02:36.531
It was such a treat for me,
going there with him.

02:38.283 --> 02:39.868
<i>But I would just-- I'd spend</i>

02:39.951 --> 02:43.955
the entire time
worrying about when...

02:45.790 --> 02:49.002
...he would stop pushing me,

02:49.085 --> 02:51.671
when he'd say
that it was time to go home.

02:55.425 --> 02:58.178
Really wish that I had spent
more time appreciating it

02:58.261 --> 03:00.805
when it was all happening,

03:00.889 --> 03:03.892
instead of just...

03:03.975 --> 03:06.603
worrying about
when it would end.

03:06.686 --> 03:08.605
Hmm.

03:08.688 --> 03:11.232
At least I still have the scar.

03:13.860 --> 03:16.279
(sighs) Oh.

03:16.363 --> 03:18.073
-Hmm.
-Um...

03:18.156 --> 03:19.532
Randall's math thing
got canceled today,

03:19.616 --> 03:22.911
so we have a completely free
Saturday with no plans.

03:23.953 --> 03:26.498
No football games,
no playdates.

03:26.581 --> 03:28.416
What should we do?

03:29.584 --> 03:30.794
Nothing.

03:30.877 --> 03:32.295
-Nothing.
-Mm-hmm.

03:32.379 --> 03:36.424
Oh, nothing sounds so nice.

03:36.508 --> 03:38.134
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

03:40.595 --> 03:43.223
And swing, Rebecca.

03:45.975 --> 03:48.812
And we swing.

03:48.895 --> 03:51.815
-Ready, Randall? (whoops)
-Kate, touch the sky.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.441
-And we swing!
-Touch the sky with your feet.

03:53.525 --> 03:54.526
There you go.

03:54.609 --> 03:56.861
♪ ♪

03:57.779 --> 04:00.990
-And we swing!
-(chuckles)

04:01.074 --> 04:03.201
-Higher!
-And we swing!

04:03.284 --> 04:04.202
(Beth whoops)

04:04.285 --> 04:05.912
<i>(Kevin laughs)</i>

04:05.995 --> 04:08.206
Swing. Throw your arms up.
(whooshes)

04:08.289 --> 04:11.001
♪ ♪

04:13.003 --> 04:14.671
-Whee!
-(Toby speaks indistinctly)

04:14.754 --> 04:17.215
-(Kate laughs)
-(gasps)

04:17.298 --> 04:18.258
All right, Hope. Ready?

04:18.341 --> 04:19.718
BOTH:
Back and forth,

04:19.801 --> 04:22.554
and we swing!

04:22.637 --> 04:25.056
-And swing!
-Swing. (chuckles)

04:25.140 --> 04:27.142
♪ ♪

04:37.110 --> 04:38.862
(birds chirping)

04:43.074 --> 04:44.909
(clicks tongue)

04:44.993 --> 04:46.578
(sighs)

04:49.247 --> 04:51.249
♪ ♪

05:01.134 --> 05:03.136
♪ ♪

05:14.147 --> 05:15.774
(sighs)

05:29.329 --> 05:30.955
(chuckles softly)

05:43.176 --> 05:45.178
♪ ♪

05:51.601 --> 05:52.519
<i>JACK:</i>
<i>Hey, guys!</i>

05:52.602 --> 05:53.812
Breakfast!

05:58.233 --> 06:00.193
-(lively chatter)
-Attention. Hello.

06:00.276 --> 06:01.444
-JACK: Mmm. Okay, Mom's up.
-So...

06:01.528 --> 06:03.613
since Randall's math contest
got canceled...

06:03.697 --> 06:05.699
-Mathletes.
-What?

06:05.782 --> 06:08.451
It's Mathletes,
and it's not a contest.

06:08.535 --> 06:09.744
It's a group of math enthusiasts

06:09.828 --> 06:12.288
who perform and compete
at a, um...

06:14.374 --> 06:15.709
Forget it.
I'll talk about it later.

06:15.792 --> 06:18.044
-Go ahead.
-It just means we have

06:18.128 --> 06:19.546
a completely free Saturday.

06:19.629 --> 06:20.755
Just us.

06:20.839 --> 06:22.257
(groans)

06:22.340 --> 06:24.134
JACK: Oh, what? Come on.
Is it really that hard

06:24.217 --> 06:26.511
-to be all together for a day?
-RANDALL AND KATE: Mm-hmm.

06:26.594 --> 06:28.680
-Yes.
-(Kate snickers)

06:28.763 --> 06:31.808
REBECCA: Okay, well,
what do you guys want to do?

06:31.891 --> 06:34.686
-Whatever.
-KEVIN: Don't care.
-(scoffs) O-Okay.

06:34.769 --> 06:36.479
Katie girl, what do you got?

06:36.563 --> 06:38.064
Anything we want?

06:38.148 --> 06:39.482
-Mm-hmm.
-All day?

06:39.566 --> 06:41.943
Anything you want. All day.

06:42.027 --> 06:43.236
What do you got, Katie girl?

06:44.571 --> 06:45.822
-Several ideas.
-REBECCA: Oh, well, there we go.

06:45.905 --> 06:47.115
Several ideas.

06:47.198 --> 06:48.700
-Okay. I like that.
-JACK: She's got ideas.

06:48.783 --> 06:50.702
I like, I like people
with several ideas.

06:50.785 --> 06:52.954
(overlapping chatter)

06:53.038 --> 06:54.914
(Randall sighs)

06:56.207 --> 06:58.418
How's the writing coming?

06:58.501 --> 06:59.627
Slowly.

07:02.297 --> 07:06.009
-Thanks.
-Service is in, uh,
less than two hours.

07:07.135 --> 07:08.511
I'm aware.

07:12.807 --> 07:14.726
(sighs heavily)

07:19.606 --> 07:20.523
What?

07:20.607 --> 07:22.359
Nothing.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.194
I'm just checking on you.

07:24.277 --> 07:25.904
I'm good.

07:26.988 --> 07:28.990
(scribbling on paper)

07:31.242 --> 07:32.660
(pen clatters)

07:32.744 --> 07:33.912
What, woman?

07:34.954 --> 07:37.707
I think we need to bang out
a worst-case scenario.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.834
-About what?
-You.

07:41.586 --> 07:43.213
You go first.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.632
I don't even know what
we're worst-case scenario-ing.

07:45.715 --> 07:48.968
After burying your fourth
and final parent, you lose it.

07:49.052 --> 07:51.805
No parents left to bury,
you spend the rest of your days

07:51.888 --> 07:53.431
going to other people's
parents' funerals.

07:53.515 --> 07:55.517
Just crying single tears

07:55.600 --> 07:57.977
at funerals of parents
you don't even know.

07:58.061 --> 07:59.104
Go.

08:00.313 --> 08:01.606
I really don't think
I'm gonna be going to...

08:01.690 --> 08:04.109
You buy an RV. (clicks tongue)

08:04.192 --> 08:06.027
Wake up one morning and say,
"Beth, we need an RV."

08:06.111 --> 08:08.238
I say, "Sure, I can get down
with an RV."

08:08.321 --> 08:10.657
You spend the rest of your days
traveling back and forth

08:10.740 --> 08:12.492
between your parents'
various resting places,

08:12.575 --> 08:14.911
just driving from tree to tree.

08:15.912 --> 08:17.956
-Baby, I'm...
-Mind you,

08:18.039 --> 08:19.708
I didn't even mention Miguel.

08:19.791 --> 08:22.335
I just realized that.
Maybe you realize it, too.

08:22.419 --> 08:25.046
-You decide you need
to go to Puerto Rico.
-(scoffs)

08:25.130 --> 08:28.008
Try and learn about his deceased
great-grandmother's story,

08:28.091 --> 08:29.217
come back talking about
swimming in the Atlantic Ocean

08:29.300 --> 08:30.635
with Miguel's
great-grandmama's ghost.

08:30.719 --> 08:31.970
-And I'm thinking to myself...
-Uh, Beth. I'm okay.

08:33.638 --> 08:35.807
I am appropriately sad,

08:35.890 --> 08:39.519
and I am appropriately anxious
about this eulogy.

08:39.602 --> 08:41.521
All right?

08:41.604 --> 08:43.273
I'm centered,

08:43.356 --> 08:46.735
and I'm looking forward
to this quiet next chapter

08:46.818 --> 08:50.488
with my wife and our lives,

08:50.572 --> 08:52.991
and our eventual grandchildren.

08:54.576 --> 08:57.328
Have you made a decision
about deep-fried Oreos?

08:58.329 --> 09:00.874
(takes deep breath)

09:00.957 --> 09:03.209
Musing.

09:03.293 --> 09:04.502
You?

09:05.545 --> 09:07.130
Same.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.550
REBECCA:
Hey, Bug, these lines looking
straight enough to you?

09:10.633 --> 09:13.553
-Yep. Perfect.
-Great.

09:13.636 --> 09:17.474
I don't want to play four square
with my parents. It's lame.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.351
Yeah, well,
you should have contributed

09:19.434 --> 09:20.685
to the suggestions, then, Kev.

09:20.769 --> 09:22.729
Kevin's right, this is stupid.

09:24.481 --> 09:25.565
What is it with you two today?

09:26.524 --> 09:28.193
Hey, ladies.

09:28.276 --> 09:30.487
Coming to check
on your chalk work.

09:30.570 --> 09:33.198
♪ ♪

09:44.584 --> 09:46.169
REBECCA:
Whoa. Oh. Right?

09:46.252 --> 09:48.254
That was an assist.
That was an assist.

09:48.338 --> 09:49.464
-(Rebecca whoops)
-(Jack laughs)

09:49.547 --> 09:51.549
-(Rebecca chuckles)
-Four big ones.

09:51.633 --> 09:53.802
♪ ♪

09:53.885 --> 09:55.804
(footsteps approaching)

09:55.887 --> 09:57.639
(chuckles softly)

10:04.854 --> 10:07.649
If it's okay with you,
I would like to say three things

10:07.732 --> 10:10.735
that will surely cross
multiple ex-husband lines

10:10.819 --> 10:12.445
and protocols.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.324
-Proceed.
-Okay.

10:16.408 --> 10:17.617
Number one.

10:19.703 --> 10:23.081
She was extraordinarily
proud of you.

10:25.333 --> 10:28.128
I am extraordinarily
proud of you.

10:28.211 --> 10:29.421
That was number two.

10:29.504 --> 10:31.548
They get progressively
more and more intense

10:31.631 --> 10:33.425
-as we go.
-Gotcha.

10:33.508 --> 10:35.510
And the third one is
a real doozy.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.263
Today is a doozy.

10:38.346 --> 10:40.807
So...

10:40.890 --> 10:43.393
I love you, kid.

10:45.895 --> 10:48.189
I love you.

10:49.232 --> 10:50.942
And even though our marriage
didn't go the distance,

10:51.026 --> 10:53.111
if Doc Brown showed up right now

10:53.194 --> 10:54.946
and offered me a ride
in the DeLorean,

10:55.030 --> 10:57.323
I would go right back to
that weight loss support group

10:57.407 --> 10:59.534
and make stupid faces at you.

10:59.617 --> 11:01.369
(chuckles)

11:01.453 --> 11:02.787
(distant chatter and laughter)

11:02.871 --> 11:04.289
That's
a <i>Back to the Future</i> reference.

11:04.372 --> 11:06.124
I know, I was married to you.

11:07.542 --> 11:08.626
Yes, you were.

11:12.380 --> 11:14.507
Yes, I was.

11:28.521 --> 11:30.023
(door opens)

11:31.483 --> 11:34.486
Kate? Kate.

11:34.569 --> 11:38.198
Thought you wanted to watch
the home movies next, right?

11:43.286 --> 11:44.996
It's raining pretty hard, huh?

11:49.417 --> 11:51.878
Hey, how about we play a game
next weekend?

11:53.880 --> 11:56.633
Better yet, how about you play
and I'll watch?

11:56.716 --> 11:59.135
I really just like
being together.

11:59.219 --> 12:02.806
Plus, only four people can play,

12:02.889 --> 12:05.141
and I just slow the game down.

12:05.225 --> 12:07.769
That's okay.

12:07.852 --> 12:12.649
I mean, all I want nowadays is
to slow things down anyway.

12:13.692 --> 12:15.276
Me, too.

12:17.821 --> 12:19.531
Home movies?

12:19.614 --> 12:21.658
-Home movies.
-Okay.

12:26.871 --> 12:27.997
(sighs)

12:30.709 --> 12:33.795
<i>-KIDS: We love cake!</i>
<i>-REBECCA: One, two, three.</i>

12:33.878 --> 12:35.255
Oh, wait. Wait, wait,
wait, wait.

12:35.338 --> 12:38.174
This-this is it.
This. Is. The. One.

12:38.258 --> 12:40.010
(VCR whirs)

12:42.178 --> 12:43.888
(Rebecca gasps)

12:43.972 --> 12:45.640
(chuckles)

12:45.724 --> 12:47.267
-REBECCA: No way.
-JACK: Uh-huh.

12:47.350 --> 12:48.560
(dishes clatter on video)

12:48.643 --> 12:49.894
Come on, not on camera, please.

12:49.978 --> 12:51.980
I'm a mess.
I'm covered in sauce.

12:52.063 --> 12:53.982
-Yeah. Oh, yeah. You know what?
You're revolting, okay?
-(chuckles)

12:54.065 --> 12:55.233
I... I want to show you
something

12:55.316 --> 12:56.526
that I've been working on.

12:56.609 --> 12:58.028
Can I just finish the dishes
first, please?

12:58.111 --> 12:59.404
Nope. Get ready.

12:59.487 --> 13:01.031
-Hey, Big Three.
-(Rebecca chuckles)

13:01.114 --> 13:02.657
Enter.

13:02.741 --> 13:04.117
Come on, come on. Come on in,
come on in.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.452
Come on in. Come on in.

13:05.535 --> 13:06.619
(Jack laughs)

13:06.703 --> 13:08.121
Come on in. Come on in, Kev.

13:08.204 --> 13:10.623
<i>-Ready?</i>
<i>-BIG THREE: Ready!</i>

13:10.707 --> 13:11.624
REBECCA:
Look at you guys.

13:11.708 --> 13:13.626
How are you that little?

13:13.710 --> 13:15.211
-JACK: So tiny.
-Look how cute you were, Kev.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.213
<i>JACK (on video):</i>
<i>Ready. First came...</i>

13:17.297 --> 13:18.715
Me.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.800
-JACK: And Dad said...
-"Gee."

13:20.884 --> 13:22.260
-JACK: And then came...
-Me.

13:22.344 --> 13:23.887
-JACK: And Mom said...
-"We."

13:23.970 --> 13:25.430
-JACK: And then came...
-Me.

13:25.513 --> 13:27.474
-JACK: And we said...
-"That's three."

13:27.557 --> 13:28.725
JACK:
Big Three.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.810
ALL:
Big Three!

13:30.894 --> 13:32.312
Ah!

13:32.395 --> 13:33.938
Jack, are you kidding me?

13:34.022 --> 13:35.690
How long did that take?

13:35.774 --> 13:36.941
JACK:
Oh, that was, uh...

13:37.025 --> 13:39.444
that was l-less than
potty training

13:39.527 --> 13:40.987
-but longer than the ABCs.
-(gasps)

13:41.071 --> 13:43.198
You guys are so good!

13:43.281 --> 13:44.491
<i>-Come give me hugs.</i>
-REBECCA: Little Kev.
-JACK: Yeah.

13:44.574 --> 13:46.659
-REBECCA: Kev, look.
-Kevin, look.

13:46.743 --> 13:48.495
<i>REBECCA (on video):</i>
<i>Oh, my goodness.</i>
<i>You're so smart.</i>

13:48.578 --> 13:49.913
I've seen this
like a million times.

13:49.996 --> 13:51.831
-Yeah.
-(Rebecca scoffs)

13:51.915 --> 13:53.249
I'm gonna go upstairs.

13:54.626 --> 13:56.127
Today sucks.

13:57.212 --> 13:59.464
(chatter on video continues)

13:59.547 --> 14:01.800
Two rays of sunshine.

14:02.842 --> 14:04.803
Knock, knock.

14:06.012 --> 14:08.098
-KEVIN: Go away.
-(scoffs)

14:09.182 --> 14:11.893
Uh-uh. Enough, Kev. Okay?

14:13.186 --> 14:15.814
Hey. What's going on, bud?

14:22.195 --> 14:24.906
Yesterday we did
the President Fitness thing.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.117
Uh-huh.

14:27.200 --> 14:30.203
I got the best time in the mile,
and I did the most sit-ups.

14:30.286 --> 14:32.872
I did just whatever
on the sit and reach, but...

14:32.956 --> 14:34.958
that's for girls anyway,
so who cares.

14:36.126 --> 14:38.253
So, what's the problem?

14:38.336 --> 14:40.964
I couldn't do any pull-ups.

14:41.047 --> 14:43.675
I've just never been
able to do them.

14:45.719 --> 14:49.556
So you can't do a pull-up.
What's the big deal?

14:49.639 --> 14:53.351
I was just hanging there
for, like, two minutes,

14:53.435 --> 14:55.395
and everyone was laughing.

14:55.478 --> 14:57.897
At me. They were laughing at me,
Mom.

14:57.981 --> 14:59.774
Okay. (clears throat)

14:59.858 --> 15:01.609
First of all,

15:01.693 --> 15:04.362
I'm sure no one was
laughing at you.

15:05.697 --> 15:08.908
Yeah. Maybe not.

15:08.992 --> 15:11.244
Plus, I had Sophie tell
a bunch of the girls

15:11.327 --> 15:14.247
that I was faking it,
so all the unathletic kids

15:14.330 --> 15:16.124
didn't feel bad
when they couldn't do one.

15:17.375 --> 15:19.461
It played.

15:19.544 --> 15:22.088
Ugh. Kevin.

15:23.131 --> 15:25.550
I really just couldn't do one,
Mom.

15:26.593 --> 15:29.054
Yeah.

15:29.137 --> 15:31.806
But that's okay.

15:31.890 --> 15:35.101
You know, not everything is
gonna come easy to you.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.979
♪ ♪

15:38.063 --> 15:39.689
<i>I think you're gonna have to</i>

15:39.773 --> 15:42.942
<i>work pretty hard</i>
<i>to become the person</i>

15:43.026 --> 15:44.819
I know you can become.

15:46.071 --> 15:49.032
And it will make
the big victories in life

15:49.115 --> 15:50.492
that much more special

15:50.575 --> 15:52.869
when you have to work
a little harder for them.

16:03.296 --> 16:04.964
Do you know
what Dr. Jaffey told us

16:05.048 --> 16:07.676
-when we went
for your last checkup?
-Hmm?

16:07.759 --> 16:10.929
He told us he thinks that
you're gonna be really tall,

16:11.012 --> 16:14.224
like over six feet tall.

16:14.307 --> 16:17.477
-Really?
-Mm-hmm. "A real jock,"
is what he said.

16:17.560 --> 16:19.604
