RANDALL:
Wrong way, wrong way, wrong way.

33:44.524 --> 33:45.859
(all clamoring)

33:45.942 --> 33:47.444
Okay, don't give her any hints,
Randall.

33:47.527 --> 33:48.528
I'm not giving her hints.

33:50.363 --> 33:53.116
There she goes.
(whooping)

33:53.199 --> 33:55.118
Katie girl, no,
are you peeking, what?

33:55.201 --> 33:56.536
-No!
-How do you do that?

33:56.619 --> 33:58.455
Bug, come on, come on,
tell us how you do that.

33:58.538 --> 33:59.914
JACK:
It's crazy.

33:59.998 --> 34:01.791
Before you put the blindfold on,

34:01.875 --> 34:03.626
I look to see
where you guys all are.

34:03.710 --> 34:05.462
And you never shut up.

34:05.545 --> 34:08.465
So as long as I know
where you are,

34:08.548 --> 34:10.550
I always know where I'm going.

34:12.719 --> 34:14.721
Baby girl.

34:20.977 --> 34:22.937
-KATE: Hey.
-Hey.

34:28.526 --> 34:30.528
(Kevin exhales)

34:34.783 --> 34:36.117
KEVIN:
You have
a creepy glow about you.

34:36.201 --> 34:37.410
(laughs)

34:37.494 --> 34:40.163
I got some good news.

34:40.246 --> 34:42.415
I got some very good news

34:42.499 --> 34:44.584
on a very sad day.

34:49.631 --> 34:52.133
(sighs)

34:53.551 --> 34:55.845
We don't have parents anymore.

34:55.929 --> 34:57.931
We still have parents.

34:58.014 --> 35:00.141
You know what I mean, though.

35:00.225 --> 35:02.769
Yeah.

35:02.852 --> 35:04.854
What are we gonna do now?

35:06.940 --> 35:09.025
Like, with our lives?

35:11.820 --> 35:14.406
We're gonna do
what she wanted us to do.

35:14.489 --> 35:16.491
We're gonna live fearlessly.

35:18.493 --> 35:20.495
I'm gonna open up
so many music schools

35:20.578 --> 35:22.163
for the visually impaired
that...

35:22.247 --> 35:24.749
People are gonna start becoming
resentful of blind musicians?

35:24.833 --> 35:26.334
-Exactly.
-Yes.

35:26.418 --> 35:28.461
They're gonna say,
"They have it too good."

35:28.545 --> 35:30.547
(all laugh)

35:32.799 --> 35:35.885
I'm gonna focus
on the nonprofit.

35:37.387 --> 35:39.097
Be home more.

35:39.180 --> 35:41.182
I like my home.

35:42.308 --> 35:44.519
Took me a long time to get it.

35:50.150 --> 35:52.944
DNC wants me to go
to the Iowa state fair.

35:53.028 --> 35:55.822
Shake some hands,
eat some junk food.

35:55.905 --> 35:58.575
Deep-fried Oreos and whatnot.

35:58.658 --> 36:00.660
And, uh...

36:00.744 --> 36:03.705
if the folks who like to
deep-fry their food like you...

36:04.956 --> 36:06.499
...then maybe...

36:08.668 --> 36:10.503
You gonna go?

36:10.587 --> 36:12.380
-I'm weighing it with Beth.
-Mm-hmm.

36:12.464 --> 36:14.257
But, uh, if she's down?

36:16.343 --> 36:18.345
For Mom?

36:19.679 --> 36:22.474
Yeah, for Mom I might go.

36:24.476 --> 36:26.644
(Kate laughs)

36:29.939 --> 36:32.317
Can I tell you guys
my nightmare?

36:35.487 --> 36:37.530
We drift.

36:37.614 --> 36:39.908
With Mom being gone
and our busy lives,

36:39.991 --> 36:41.409
we drift.

36:41.493 --> 36:42.786
And I'm not saying we wind up,

36:42.869 --> 36:44.329
you know,
estranged or anything, but...

36:44.412 --> 36:47.040
We're not gonna drift.

36:47.123 --> 36:49.626
We could drift.

36:58.009 --> 37:00.387
Secret.
(clears throat)

37:00.470 --> 37:03.181
If someone asks me
to close my eyes

37:03.264 --> 37:05.892
and picture my family...

37:05.975 --> 37:08.895
it's not Beth and the girls
I see first.

37:10.355 --> 37:12.440
My first picture is Mom and Dad

37:12.524 --> 37:14.567
and the two of you.

37:16.569 --> 37:19.906
Younger, cuter versions
of you two, but still...

37:20.949 --> 37:23.743
-Same.
-Same.

37:26.996 --> 37:28.998
Guys?

37:31.209 --> 37:33.211
First came?

37:35.672 --> 37:37.465
Me.

37:37.549 --> 37:40.176
-And Dad said?
-Gee.

37:40.260 --> 37:42.595
-And then came?
-Me.

37:42.679 --> 37:44.514
-And Mom said?
-We.

37:44.597 --> 37:46.141
-(chuckles)
-And then came?

37:46.224 --> 37:48.226
Me.

37:49.227 --> 37:50.770
And they said?

37:50.854 --> 37:53.023
That's three.

37:53.106 --> 37:54.941
ALL:
Big Three.

37:56.776 --> 37:58.778
Big Three.

38:04.325 --> 38:06.578
(sighs)

38:09.205 --> 38:11.207
Hey, Kate?

38:13.710 --> 38:16.546
If you drifted...

38:16.629 --> 38:19.049
we'd drift right after you.

38:20.467 --> 38:22.469
Aw.

38:24.596 --> 38:26.348
Can you really drift,
though, Kev?

38:26.431 --> 38:28.016
'Cause I can't remember

38:28.099 --> 38:29.559
if you ever actually
learned how to swim.

38:29.642 --> 38:31.102
(both laugh)

38:31.186 --> 38:33.063
Yeah, well,
I had to learn how to swim.

38:33.146 --> 38:34.856
Growing up with you, all those
tears, I would've drowned.

38:34.939 --> 38:36.983
-Right in the kitchen.
-I'm sorry, I'm just in touch

38:37.067 --> 38:38.735
-with my emotions
unlike some people, Robo-Kev.
-Yeah, I'm just saying,

38:38.818 --> 38:40.987
you know, people don't like
their presidents all weepy

38:41.071 --> 38:43.406
and stuff, you know what I mean,
you got to button that up.

38:47.494 --> 38:50.288
She grabbed my hand.

38:50.372 --> 38:52.374
Hard.

38:52.457 --> 38:54.334
Right at the very end.

38:54.417 --> 38:56.419
You know, right before...

38:57.712 --> 38:59.172
Yeah.

38:59.255 --> 39:01.132
I know, I saw.

39:02.133 --> 39:04.135
I wonder what that was.

39:06.388 --> 39:08.390
(train rattling)

39:15.772 --> 39:17.357
Hey.

39:18.566 --> 39:20.819
Hey.

39:25.448 --> 39:26.866
Mm.

39:32.205 --> 39:34.416
I've missed that little scar.

39:35.583 --> 39:37.627
Come on, you didn't even
notice it for over a decade.

39:37.711 --> 39:41.089
Was too busy looking
at the rest of the face.

39:47.679 --> 39:49.889
I'm scared.

39:49.973 --> 39:52.267
I know.

39:52.350 --> 39:55.103
But don't be.

39:57.105 --> 39:59.024
KEVIN:
Okay.

39:59.107 --> 40:01.026
Let's be honest,
now that I'm shaving,

40:01.109 --> 40:03.069
do I seem more like a man?

40:03.153 --> 40:05.113
-No.
-More like Dad?

40:05.196 --> 40:06.948
-You're getting there.
-I don't know, Kev.

40:07.032 --> 40:08.575
I don't,
I don't really see it yet.

40:08.658 --> 40:11.119
You do know how much
I love you, right, Bec?

40:11.202 --> 40:12.454
Babe?

40:12.537 --> 40:13.830
-JACK: Bec?
-REBECCA: Who, me?

40:13.913 --> 40:15.582
Babe, do you, do you know
how much I love you?

40:15.665 --> 40:18.251
You got, you got to appreciate
the little things, Bec.

40:18.335 --> 40:19.461
Babe, you have said that before.

40:19.544 --> 40:20.795
He was, he was listening
to what I said.

40:20.879 --> 40:22.756
He says it all the time.

40:22.839 --> 40:24.966
-Those are big things...
-No, the little things...

40:25.050 --> 40:27.302
(all clamoring)

40:27.385 --> 40:29.679
-Hey, babe?
-Yeah.

40:29.763 --> 40:32.057
We did good.

40:32.140 --> 40:33.933
You...

40:34.017 --> 40:36.061
did so good.

40:37.937 --> 40:40.398
There was so much left
I wanted to do with them.

40:40.482 --> 40:42.359
You will.

40:42.442 --> 40:44.778
All right, go easy on me.
Oh, boy.

40:44.861 --> 40:47.614
Oh... boy.

40:47.697 --> 40:50.075
(all chatting, clamoring)

40:50.158 --> 40:52.160
What?

40:52.243 --> 40:54.996
It's hard to explain,

40:55.080 --> 40:56.539
but...

40:56.623 --> 40:58.875
you'll do all those things
with them.

40:58.958 --> 41:00.877
♪ ♪

41:03.129 --> 41:04.923
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>Promise?</i>

41:05.006 --> 41:06.925
I do.

41:07.008 --> 41:09.427
I mean, it's not
like I want to be there

41:09.511 --> 41:11.221
for anything weird.

41:11.304 --> 41:13.765
I don't want to watch them
shower or anything.

41:13.848 --> 41:15.308
You won't.

41:15.392 --> 41:17.102
But you'll be there.

41:23.483 --> 41:25.485
♪ ♪

41:27.737 --> 41:29.989
OTHERS:
Oh!

41:31.908 --> 41:33.284
(all clamoring, laughing)

41:33.368 --> 41:35.203
Oh!

41:35.286 --> 41:36.996
I can't dance.

41:37.080 --> 41:38.581
Just focus on the kids.
No, no, no,

41:38.665 --> 41:40.083
no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

41:40.166 --> 41:41.501
No! No! No! No! No! No!

41:41.584 --> 41:44.004
(laughing, clamoring)

41:44.087 --> 41:46.131
<i>Quite a thing, isn't it?</i>

41:47.382 --> 41:49.259
Us...

41:49.342 --> 41:51.678
finding each other
in that bar that night.

41:52.679 --> 41:55.015
I don't know.

41:55.098 --> 41:57.058
I mean, when the world

41:57.142 --> 41:59.394
puts something that obvious
in front of you,

41:59.477 --> 42:01.813
you don't just walk away.

42:01.896 --> 42:03.898
♪ ♪

42:05.150 --> 42:07.318
(laughing, clamoring)

42:09.404 --> 42:11.614
Get Randall!
Get Randall! Get Randall!

42:11.698 --> 42:13.241
(Randall shouting)

42:13.324 --> 42:14.826
<i>JACK:</i>
<i>You ready?</i>

42:17.203 --> 42:19.205
I don't want to leave them.

42:19.289 --> 42:21.374
You don't.

42:21.458 --> 42:23.918
You'll see.

42:26.129 --> 42:28.423
I love you.

42:29.632 --> 42:31.634
I love you.

